<reference anchor="I-D.shawam-pwe3-ms-pw-protection" target="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-shawam-pwe3-ms-pw-protection-00">
  <front>
    <title>Encapsulation for PSC for Multi-Segment Pseudowires</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-shawam-pwe3-ms-pw-protection-00"/>
    <author initials="H." surname="van Helvoort" fullname="Huub van Helvoort"/>
    <author initials="L." surname="Andersson" fullname="Loa Andersson"/>
    <author initials="A. G." surname="Malis" fullname="Andrew G. Malis"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Shin" fullname="Jongyoon Shin"/>
    <author initials="L." surname="Wang" fullname="Lei Wang"/>
    <author initials="A." surname="D'Alessandro" fullname="Alessandro D'Alessandro"/>
    <date day="01" month="July" year="2014"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>In RFC 6378 'MPLS Transport Profile (MPLS-TP) Linear Protection', as
   well as in the later updates of this RFC, the Protection State
   Coordiantion (PSC) protocol was defined for MPLS LSPs only.  This
   draft extends RFC 6378 to be applicable for pseudowires as well.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
</reference>